---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FeedbackWidget from '../components/FeedbackWidget.astro';
---
<Layout title="Ship with AI">
  <h1>Ship with AI: Review, Secure, and Deploy with Confidence</h1>
  <p>
    AI writes more code, faster than ever. That's the easy part. The hard part — the part that
    decides whether shipping with AI is safe — is what happens next: who reviews it, who secures
    it, and how it gets from a pull request to production without anyone's attention slipping.
  </p>
  <p>
    This site is both things at once. It's the companion material for AI Genius Season 5,
    Episode 3, and it's also the exact repository that was reviewed, secured, and deployed live
    on stream, using the pipeline described on the next few pages.
  </p>
  <div class="card">
    <strong>The trust gap.</strong> The more code an AI assistant produces, the more your review,
    security, and release process has to carry. Speed without those guardrails just moves risk
    downstream — into your dependencies, your CI/CD pipeline, and your production environment.
  </div>
  <h2>Where to start</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="pipeline/">The pipeline</a> — how an idea becomes a deployed change</li>
    <li><a href="secure-supply-chain/">Secure your supply chain</a> — the security spine of this demo</li>
    <li><a href="diy/">Do it yourself</a> — turn all of this on in your own repo</li>
  </ul>
  <FeedbackWidget />
</Layout>
